    <h2>Why Face Puffiness Happens (And Why You Care)</h2>
    <p>Puffiness under your eyes and around your face typically results from fluid retention, inflammation, poor circulation, or inadequate sleep. Morning puffiness is particularly frustrating because it can make you look tired and less polished, affecting how you feel about your appearance before a big meeting or event.</p>

