    <!-- How to Use Section -->
    <h2>How to Use the Stainless Steel Face Roller (Properly)</h2>
    <p>Most people don't get results with face rollers because they use them incorrectly. Here's the right technique:</p>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>Prep:</strong> Freeze or refrigerate the roller for at least 2-4 hours (or overnight for best results).</li>
      <li><strong>Cleanse:</strong> Wash your face with a gentle cleanser and pat dry. Apply a lightweight serum or moisturizer if desired.</li>
      <li><strong>Gentle pressure:</strong> Using minimal pressure (imagine rolling a feather, not rolling out dough), start at your inner cheekbones and roll upward and outward toward your temples.</li>
      <li><strong>Under-eye focus:</strong> Gently roll from the inner corner of your eye outward along the orbital bone. Avoid direct eye contact.</li>
      <li><strong>Jawline and neck:</strong> Roll upward along your jawline and down your neck to stimulate lymphatic drainage.</li>
      <li><strong>Duration:</strong> 3-5 minutes total is sufficient. Longer isn't better.</li>
      <li><strong>Frequency:</strong> Use daily for best results, preferably in the morning.</li>
      <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Rinse with water after each use and store in the freezer.</li>
    </ol>

