    <!-- Tradeoffs Section -->
    <h2>Key Tradeoffs to Understand</h2>
    <p><strong>Cold Effect vs. Convenience:</strong> The longer you refrigerate this roller, the better the cold retention—but convenience suffers. Most users find 4 hours of freezing time (overnight) to be the sweet spot.</p>

    <p><strong>Results vs. Expectations:</strong> Face rollers deliver real, measurable benefits—but only for puffiness and temporary appearance improvements. If you're expecting wrinkle reduction or permanent firmness gains, you'll be disappointed. Those require professional treatments (Botox, dermal fillers, microneedling).</p>

    <p><strong>Cost vs. Durability:</strong> At $19.99, this is incredibly affordable. The stainless steel construction means you'll likely use it for years, making the per-use cost negligible. However, the cheap price point means some users may not take it seriously.</p>

    <!-- Final Verdict -->
    <h2>Final Verdict: Is It Worth $19.99?</h2>
    <p>Absolutely. The Stainless Steel Face Roller from Vibe Test Lab is one of the best sub-$20 skincare tools you can buy. It delivers on its primary promise—reducing puffiness—and the stainless steel construction actually outperforms pricier gemstone alternatives in terms of cold retention and hygiene.</p>

    <p>Where it fails is in the broader anti-aging category. This won't replace professional treatments, won't permanently improve skin texture, and won't reduce fine lines. But for what it costs and what it's designed to do, it's excellent value.</p>

    <p><strong>Who should buy:</strong> Anyone dealing with morning puffiness, anyone who enjoys skincare rituals, anyone on a budget looking for a legitimate tool.</p>

    <p><strong>Who should skip:</strong> Anyone expecting permanent anti-aging results, anyone unwilling to refrigerate between uses, anyone with active skin conditions who need to avoid cold exposure.</p>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">Can I use the face roller on acne-prone skin?</div>
      <div class="faq-answer">Proceed with caution. If you have active breakouts, the cold can actually help reduce inflammation—but the rolling motion may spread bacteria or irritate existing lesions. If you have mild acne, use very light pressure and avoid rolling directly over active pimples. For severe acne, consult your dermatologist first. The cold itself can provide relief for inflamed skin, making it potentially beneficial for some people.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">How long does the puffiness reduction last?</div>
      <div class="faq-answer">Typically 2-4 hours after use, depending on room temperature, your hydration level, and how much sleep you got. The cold effect wears off first (within 30 minutes), but the massage benefits from improved circulation persist longer. For longest-lasting results, use in the morning and avoid excessive salt intake the night before.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">Can I use serums or moisturizers with it?</div>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes, absolutely. In fact, using the roller over a lightweight serum or moisturizer can enhance absorption (though the "pressing serums into skin" concept is somewhat exaggerated). The massage motion does help distribute products more evenly across your face. Avoid using it with heavy creams or oils, which can cause the roller to slip.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">Is stainless steel safe for skin?</div>
      <div class="faq-answer">Completely safe. Grade 304 stainless steel is hypoallergenic and non-reactive. It's the same material used in surgical instruments and medical implants. It won't cause allergic reactions or sensitize your skin. Its non-porous nature also means it won't accumulate bacteria like porous stones do.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">How often should I use it?</div>
      <div class="faq-answer">Daily use is safe and recommended for best results. Many users incorporate it into their morning routine (3-5 minutes). You can also use it at night, though morning use targets the morning puffiness most people struggle with. If your skin is sensitive, start with 3-4 times per week and gradually increase.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-question">Will it really reduce wrinkles or improve skin texture?</div>
      <div class="faq-answer">No—this is where expectations need to be realistic. Face rollers do not increase collagen production, permanently improve skin texture, or reduce fine lines. The temporary "glow" effect comes from improved circulation, which fades. For wrinkle reduction, you'll need professional treatments like microneedling, laser therapy, or injectables. Face rollers are a maintenance tool, not a treatment.</div>
    </div>

